load dev actor/policy fixture
initialize local node and registry records
register fixture repo
create placement record for fixture repo
open workspace
read/search/update repository files through SDK
run remote shell search if needed
commit changes with Gitoxide-backed path where practical
refresh graph into TreeDB-native segments
query graph through SDK
verify unauthorized query scope is reduced before graph/search access
build repository snapshot
simulate mirror placement/sync state
restart service
verify catalog/policy/placement/audit/graph/snapshot recovery
check audit events
```

## Regression Rules

* Existing SDK local mode tests must keep passing.
* TreeDB remote mode must be additive until proven stable.
* Any SDK type changes must have migration notes.
* Any TreeDB endpoint changes must update OpenAPI and SDK tests in the same commit.
* Any TreeDB storage format change must include a version/migration note.
* Any auth/policy storage format change must include a version/migration note.
* Any federation/placement format change must include a version/migration note.
* Any shell Git fallback must include an issue or tracking note for Gitoxide replacement.
* No TreeDB test should require knowledge-pack, template, listing, or other product-domain semantics.

