## Security and Safety MVP

### Required Before Any Shared Environment

* Token verification or explicitly configured dev-token mode.
* Effective scope resolution for every request.
* Repo/path/ref authorization checks.
* Registry/mirror/migration authorization checks.
* Path normalization and traversal protection.
* Capability checks for every endpoint.
* Workspace TTL and cleanup.
* Command timeout and output cap.
* Disallowed path globs.
* Environment scrubbing for shell execution.
* Audit events for all mutations and exec requests.
* Commit API separate from shell API.
* No arbitrary push/mirror/migration through shell.
* TreeDB data directory permissions checked on startup.
* TreeDB data directory lock to prevent unsafe multi-process writes.
* Recovery mode for interrupted writes.

### Required Before Untrusted Agents

* Stronger sandboxing than direct host process execution.
* Network isolation.
* Resource isolation.
* Secret isolation.
* Per-tenant repository separation.
* Production-grade token verification/key rotation.
* Policy refresh and revocation propagation.
* Stronger storage-level corruption detection and backup/export story.
* Mirror promotion/failover safety review.
* Federated query leakage review.

