## Developer Experience Goals

The canonical developer experience should require Docker, not a host Erlang/Elixir/Rust/Node toolchain.

Primary commands:

```bash
docker compose build treedb-api
docker compose up treedb-api
docker compose exec treedb-api mix test
docker compose exec treedb-api cargo test --workspace
```

Convenience wrappers may be added:

```bash
make setup
make test
make dev
```

Or package-native equivalents:

```bash
scripts/setup.sh
scripts/test-all.sh
scripts/dev.sh
```

The wrappers should call Docker Compose by default.

Developer should be able to run:

```bash
# start TreeDB with hot reload and persistent data volume
docker compose up treedb-api

# inspect the TreeDB data directory inside the container
docker compose exec treedb-api ls -la /var/lib/treedb

# request a dev token and inspect effective scope
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/api/v1/auth/dev-token
curl http://localhost:4000/api/v1/policy/effective-scope

# inspect local node and repository placement
curl http://localhost:4000/api/v1/node
curl http://localhost:4000/api/v1/registry/nodes

# run SDK tests against TreeDB
cd packages/ts-sdk && TREEDB_URL=http://localhost:4000 npm test
```

Optional host-local development can remain documented for maintainers who already have the toolchains installed:

```bash
export TREEDB_DATA_DIR=/tmp/treedb-dev
cd apps/api && mix phx.server
```

But host-local development should not be the canonical path.

