## Suggested First Implementation Sprint

### Sprint Goal

Prove TreeDB can be launched as a containerized hot-reload service with an explicit persistent data volume, prove a fixture actor can authenticate and receive an effective repository scope, initialize local node/registry state, and prove a stateless TypeScript SDK client can update a file in a Git repository through TreeDB and receive a commit SHA, without cloning the repository locally, without PostgreSQL/SQLite, and without shell Git for basic repository inspection.

### Scope

* Root Dockerfile with `dev` and `prod` targets.
* Root `compose.yaml` with `treedb-api` service and `treedb-data` volume.
* Phoenix service skeleton running through Docker Compose.
* Hot reload support through source bind mount.
* TreeDB data directory initialization at `/var/lib/treedb`.
* Dev-token/local policy fixture.
* Local node manifest.
* Local registry/placement catalog files.
* `treedb_store` repository catalog file.
* `treedb_store` policy/access catalog files.
* `treedb_store` append-only audit log.
* `treedb_git` fixture repo open/remote/ref/tree/blob reads through Gitoxide/gix.
* Repository registration with authorized actor.
* Repository placement record with local node as primary.
* Workspace create/close with effective-scope snapshot.
* File read/write/status/diff/commit.
* Minimal `TreeDbClient` and placement read in `packages/ts-sdk`.
* One end-to-end test.

### Out of Scope

* Production-grade token verification/key rotation.
* Full federated query implementation.
* Multi-node mirror sync.
* Mirror promotion/failover.
* Full graph indexing.
* Higher-level product model semantics.
* Remote shell.
* Production sandboxing.
* Multi-node replication.
* Fully optimized overlay workspaces.

### Sprint Acceptance Test

```ts
const client = new TreeDbClient({ baseUrl, repoId, token, defaultActor });

const whoami = await client.whoami();
expect(whoami.actor.id).toBeTruthy();

const node = await client.getNode();
expect(node.nodeId).toBeTruthy();

const placement = await client.getPlacement(repoId);
expect(placement.primary.nodeId).toEqual(node.nodeId);

const scope = await client.effectiveScope({ repoId });
expect(scope.capabilities).toContain("workspace:create");

const workspace = await client.createWorkspace({
  baseRef: "refs/heads/main",
  branchName: "refs/heads/agent/demo-update",
  mode: "writable",
  allowedPaths: ["src/content/**"]
});

await client.writeFile({
  workspaceId: workspace.id,
  path: "src/content/demo.mdx",
  content: "---
title: Demo
---

Updated by TreeDB.
"
});

const diff = await client.diff({ workspaceId: workspace.id });

const commit = await client.commit({
  workspaceId: workspace.id,
  message: "Update demo file through TreeDB"
});

expect(commit.commitSha).toBeTruthy();
expect(commit.changedPaths).toContain("src/content/demo.mdx");
```

